article.headline: Northeastern 67, James Madison 64
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- Eugene Spates had a career-high 21 points, including 15 in the second half, to lead Northeastern to its first road win of the season with a 67-64 victory over James Madison on Saturday night. The Huskies (9-17, 7-8 Colonial Athletic Association) trailed 50-38 with 16:22 to play, but went on an 21-8 run to take a 59-58 lead with 4:29 left. The Dukes (7-18, 4-11) tied it 59-all seconds later on a pair of free throws keep it to within one with 2:10 to play, but were unable to regain the lead. Northeastern kept the Dukes scoreless in the final minutes and held the lead on free throws from Spates and Matt Janning. Bobby Kelly added 13 points for the Huskies, Bennet Davis had 12 and Janning had 11. Pierre Curtis led James Madison with a career-high 20 points and Juwann James added 18.
